        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 5:03PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 503 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Brush, or 5 miles east of Fort Morgan, moving southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Morgan, Brush, Log Lane Village, Hillrose, Gary, Adena
School, Twelve-Mile Corner, Woodrow, Snyder, Adena, Midway, Union
and Fremont Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
